	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am missin your point here. Just because it took to someone loads of time and cash to get the skill up, why should I care? No one forced them to spend all this money and time on this, they did it on their own. This is stupidest excuse I have so far heard! &quot;Because it took me so much time and so much resources, waah-waah...&quot;, what a joke.<br><br>By your description, a person may born and decide since childhood that he/she wants to become a good businesman. He/she learns all his/her life, graduates one school after another, university after another, and then, finally, after all these years and money, opens a business and starts to charge some crazy cash with the excuse &quot;But I spent so much time and money for this!&quot;?? Heh, a good joke indeed.<br><br>Neither is anyone supposed to pay you for your failures. It costs a crapload to buy the items, you offer to provide the service, then you also better darn do it, and provide the product. If you fail and lose the &quot;parts&quot;, these will come out of YOUR pocket. You said you will make it, now make it. Deliver what you promised. And save the whines &quot;the skill was soo expensive to raise, so I charge you with the 200% added cash to the price of materials&quot;. That's BS.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Apr 29 07:19:44 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
