<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102010149192295></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102010149192295><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4257&mid=102010149192295>RE: Re:Huh?</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4257&mid=102010149192295#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=92601><span id=Guru>Feldaer</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>170 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 29th 1:38 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.37]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually, the first guy makes sense and you are the one in left field. Lets look at the real world. Think of high end jewelry-making as comparable to the pharmaceutical industry. They spend a lot of money on drug research, and most of the attempts fail. So when they do succeed, they charge a buttload for the new drugs, because they can cure things that no other drugs can. Think of each attempt on a velium jewelry item as the equivalent of a drug research trial. Costs a lot, and even at your best, it will fail as often as succeed. So when you do succeed, you charge enough to cover the average cost of failure, and a little profit for your time.<br><br>And just like the real world, everyone whines about the cost, but will pay it, because there is no other alternative. If drug costs were not so high, pharm companies would cease to do research. Similarly, if these items were not priced to cover costs + add some profit, who the heck would make them. I don't do jewelry, but am a smith and tailor, so I appreciate their effort. I have rings, earrings and a veil made by jewelcraft, and there are no similar items available anywhere, for even close to the price i paid. So it didn't cost the jeweler 600pp to make my plat/ruby veil. big deal. I like it, it was worth 600pp to me. Show me a better face item for a cleric (or druid for that matter), that isn't high end planes or raid type gear.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
